      • copyFile

        public static void copyFile(java.io.File source,
                            java.io.File destination)
                     throws java.io.IOException
        Copies a file or folder to destination and automatically creates all parents folders if they don't exist.

        If you try to copy a directory A in a destination B, the content of A will be copied in B. If you really want a copy of A within B, then set the destination as B + File.separator + A.
        Parameters:
        source - File or directory to copy
        destination - Destination
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
